### Post/Redirect/Get

- Post/Redirect/Get (PRG)
  - a software design pattern used in web development to prevent
   duplicate form submissions.

- The Problem:
  - When a user submits a form (POST request) and refreshes the
    confirmation page, the browser often asks to resubmit the data,
    which can lead to duplicate database entries or orders.

- The Solution:
  - Instead of directly returning an HTML page after a POST request,
    the server sends a "Redirect" (3xx status code) to a new URL.
    The browser then performs a "GET" request to that new URL.

- Result:
  - If the user refreshes the final page, they are only refreshing
    the GET request, not resubmitting the form data.

